1 olive oil
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bag herbs
1 tomato
1 cucumber
½ bottle cream
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 bottle Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 packet Roasted Potatoes with Garlic Herb Butter
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
medium-high heat
• Cook pork and seasoning, until
cooked through, 3-4 mins each side
• Transfer to plate, cover and rest for
5 mins
• Finely chop herbs, tomato and
cucumber

• Prick a few holes in potato packet.
Microwave until soft and steaming,
4-5 mins
• Return pan to low-medium heat with
a drizzle of oil. Add cream
(1/2 bottle for 2P / 1 bottle for 4P)
and herbs and cook until slightly
reduced, 1-2 mins
• Remove pan from heat, then stir
through cheese

• In a bowl, combine tomato,
cucumber, mixed leaves and
dressing. Season
• Plate up potato, pork and salad
• Spoon sauce over pork to serve